org.sbml.jsbml.ext.layout

Class Curve

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.sbml.jsbml.AbstractTreeNode
      • org.sbml.jsbml.AbstractSBase
        • org.sbml.jsbml.AbstractNamedSBase
          • org.sbml.jsbml.ext.layout.Curve
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, TreeNode, NamedSBase, SBase, TreeNodeWithChangeSupport

    public class Curve
extends AbstractNamedSBase
    The Curve class describes how to connect elements in a diagram defined with the use of the Layout package. A curve is fully specified by a mandatory listOfCurveSegments element and is used in four places in the Layout package: SpeciesReferenceGlyph, ReactionGlyph, ReferenceGlyph, and GeneralGlyph.
